events.name: Machine Learning Study Jams at GDG Surat

venue.name: Raksh Infotech
venue.address_1: 4040, 4th Floor, The Palladium, Above Dhiraj Sons,Yogichowk, Varachha

events.description:
[Important] Including RSVP, Registration is also mandatory. Registered participants will be welcomed only. So Kindly Register yourself to attend this event.
Registration Link: http://bit.ly/2A3pXrS

What is machine learning? What is AI? It turns out that these words have multiple meanings... and when businesses don’t know the differences, they run into a world of problems. We’ll go back to basics and strip away the jargon to see what’s really behind the magician’s stand-in simple analogies. Let’s take a look at what’s easy, what’s hard, how to spot opportunities, and what you need to know to avoid the two biggest threats in AI. Along the way, we’ll meet an emerging discipline that focuses on using machine learning and AI to improve your business: decision intelligence engineering! Moreover, we'll talk about Tensorflow and it's applications.

MLCC is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable them to use machine learning within their everyday projects, and who wish to benefit from the power of TensorFlow wrapped in convenient higher-level abstractions.
This is a great opportunity for an audience with basic technical knowledge and limited Machine Learning knowledge willing to gain some practical experience in ML and TensorFlow.

venue.name: Spaceplexx Coworking
venue.address_1: Spaceplexx Coworking, 205, SNS Platina, Behind J.H. Ambani School, Vesu

events.description:
Want to start developing with flutter, but don't know how to start?

Register: http://bit.ly/flutterstudyjamsurat

Speaker: Parth Jansari
Event Date: 23rd December 2018
Time: 1:00 PM to 4:30 PM
Venue: Spaceplexx Coworking
Address: 205 SNS Platina, Behind JH Ambani School, Someshwara Enclave, Vesu, Surat, Gujarat[masked]
Map Location: https://goo.gl/maps/3sZTetLVDft

*What is flutter*

Flutter is Google’s mobile app SDK for crafting high-quality native
interfaces on iOS and Android in record time. Flutter works with existing
code, is used by developers and organizations around the world, and is
free and open source.
Want to get started on building Flutter apps?

*About the study jam*

Join us for our Flutter Study Jam! Together we'll work through Flutter
Udacity Course prepared by Google instructors.

We have an amazing facilitator

*What you will learn*
You will be able to get
hands-on experience with Flutter and build a Flutter app while learning
the fundamentals.

At the end of the study jam, you should be comfortable working with flutter and showcase your project on github

*Requirements*

Bring a laptop! The course will run on all of the latest versions of the
popular browsers. For the best experience, the laptop should have
Flutter installed on it prior to starting the study jam to save time.

*PLEASE NOTE ONLY REGISTERED and RSVPed ATTENDEES WILL BE ALLOWED INTO THE VENUE BECAUSE OF THE SPACE CONSTRAINT WE HAVE, THIS TO AVOID EMBARRASSMENT AT THE GATE. THANKS FOR COMPLYING*

Windows/Linux/Mac would all be fine. Check out :
https://flutter.io/get-started/install/
